This paper deals with uncertainty estimation in object detection using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of sampling-based techniques, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The merging and clustering methods used in the paper are related to robotics (cs.RO) and computer security (cs.CR), respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.CR.
